          <title>Clemente Jr. unhappy about Pirates removing sign honoring his Hall of Fame father at PNC Park</title>
          <description><![CDATA[PITTSBURGH (AP) — The Pittsburgh Pirates have angered the family of the late Roberto Clemente by removing a sign honoring the franchise icon on the right-field wall at PNC Park. The sign featured Clemente’s name and his No. 21. Replacing it is an advertisement for Surfside, an alcoholic drink.]]></description>
